---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="eyebrow">About</div>
    <h1>Notes on how I work</h1>
    <p class="hero-lede">
      I'm Hankyeol Kyung, an AI/agent engineer building practical systems for
      memory, runtime, and human-AI collaboration, from product surfaces to the infrastructure underneath them.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">Where I work</span>
    <p>
      I'm on the product team at <a href="https://asleep.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Asleep</a>,
      where I work on SleepHub, an ambient AI product for autonomous sleep coaching and tracking.
      My work tends to sit where applied AI meets product infrastructure, deployment reality,
      and the systems that make AI useful outside of staged demos.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">How I think about work</span>
    <p>
      I care about runtime correctness, context continuity, and making AI collaboration
      surfaces that feel real rather than demo-shaped. Most of my work sits at the intersection
      of applied AI, product infrastructure, and validation, the kind of work that has to ship,
      stay running, and survive real usage.
    </p>
    <p>
      I prefer explicit over implicit, inspectable over opaque, and boring technology I can debug
      over novelty I can't. Markdown files beat opaque stores. Plain scripts beat frameworks.
      When something feels magical, I usually want to see the seams.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">What I'm building outside the day job</span>
    <p>
      I write about agents, memory, runtime behavior, and the architecture of human-AI collaboration on
      <a href="/writing">Writing</a>. I also maintain a personal Knowledge OS that this site is generated from,
      a markdown-first system for turning private context into reusable task context and selected public artifacts.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">Get in touch</span>
    <p>
      The easiest public surfaces are <a href="https://github.com/keenranger">GitHub</a> and
      <a href="https://x.com/hankyeolkyung">X</a>. If you're working on agent runtimes, memory systems,
      ambient AI, or anything in that neighborhood, I'd enjoy hearing from you.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
